Introduction

Yeeun, also known as Jang Yeeun, is a South Korean rapper and singer-songwriter under SuperBell Company. She used to be a part of the girl group CLC and a member of the project girl group EL7Z UP.

On March 19, 2015, she debuted as a CLC member with the release of the group’s first mini album “First Love”. Her representative fruit in the group was Tomato. In May 2020, she became a contestant on the survival show Good Girl. She departed CUBE Entertainment and concluded her contract which expired on March 18, 2022.

On August 11, 2022, she signed with SuperBell Company as a soloist. On April 13, 2023, she debuted as a soloist with the single album "The Beginning".

On April 24, 2023, she participated in the survival show Queendom Puzzle and finished in 7th place earning her spot in the project girl group EL7Z UP. They made their debut on September 14, 2023, with their first mini album “7+Up”.
